{
  "texts": [
    "Sample quotas on gender, age, ethnicity, education, and income were specified to match those demographic distributions in the U.S. population.",
    "Sample quotas on gender and age were specified to match those demographic distributions in the U.S. population.",
    "Our survey reflects a sample (N = 1150) with quotas on gender (54.1% female), age (M = 50.09, SD = 18.17), race (62.2% White/ Caucasian), income (64.3% made $75,000 or less), education (43.9% had some college degree or less), and employment status (31.6% were employed by an organization).",
    "According to the 2020 census data, the final sample's demographics closely match that of the general U.S. population (U.S. Census Bureau 2020).",
    "Compared to the U.S. census data, our sample is slightly older (people 55+ years old constitute 30% in census data versus 44% in our sample) and more educated (people with 4-year degree constitute 38% in census data versus 44% in our sample)."
  ]
}